# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# [FILE] .gitignore
# [VERSION] 1.0.0 (Academic/Data Science Release)
# [DESCRIPTION] Defines build artifacts, secrets, and large data 
#               exclusions to keep the academic repository clean.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- 1. Python & Virtual Environments (The Noise) ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
venv/
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# --- 2. System Artifacts ---
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Thumbs.db

# --- 3. Secrets & Security (CRITICAL) ---
# [SECURITY] Never commit the vault password or unencrypted secrets
.vault_pass
.ansible_vault_password
.env
*.retry
infra/ansible/inventory/host_vars/secret_*.yml

# --- 4. Research Data (The Bloat) ---
# Raw logs are too big for Git. We track the generated reports instead.
research_data/
data/
storage_history.csv

# [DATA SCIENCE] Ignore intermediate ML outputs, keep "Gold Standard"
analysis/*
!analysis/daily_reports/
!analysis/archive/
!analysis/**/*.md

# --- 5. Documentation & Showcase ---
# Ensure our academic proofs are always tracked
!docs/showcase/
# Optional: Ignore specific automated run folders if they get too numerous
# docs/showcase/run_*/

# --- 6. Infrastructure Volumes ---
infra/database/data/
mosquitto/data/
mosquitto/log/
influxdb/
opensearch/

# --- 7. Large Binaries & Models ---
*.pt
*.onnx
*.tflite
*.tar.gz
*.zip
docs/showcase/archive/
docs/showcase/archive/
